&lt;td&gt;Not in any way will I care about the hardship in the wilds if I follow you.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;275&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b2-6&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;If you see the two ornamented with flower strings … you cannot remember kinghood; (if you see) the two childish ones (playing) in the salty bushes … you cannot think about the royal rank and worth. (If you) … the [appropriate] season …, the good and the bad season … if you see the … that cause joys; the courses (?) of the water dug by nature … as if sitting among … you will certainly enjoy yourself. (cf [[Carling, DThTA]]: 135a)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;644&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3&lt;/b&gt;: here as in [[Carling, DThTA]]: 132; &lt;i&gt;paying&lt;/i&gt; in ibid, p. 31 (TI)&lt;/p&gt;
