               <item n="m_translation_old">a1 ... not caring about their being separated, wiping away the tears, she says to her husband: Oh lord,
a2 ... (It would not be right) for you to go to the forest alone. Therefore, in whichever direction you will go
a3 (there I will go too). ... in no way will I pay attention to the exertion in the forest, not even ...
a4 ... || In the ?-tune:|| The forests [are] free from evil beings, not by anyone
a5 (are its creeks and rivers appreciated) ... as if covered with a carpet of beryl, with lovely spaces of grass
a6 ... If I am together with the children [and] yourself, I will not be worried about... (?)
b1 ... (even you) will not be annoyed by going to the forest (together with the sons), because ...
b2 ... || In the ?.-tune: || When you see the two, adorned with ribbons of flowers,
b3 ... [you] will (not) be able to remember [your] kingship. (When you see (?)) the two childish ones (playing) in the salty bushes
b4 ... you will not think of [your] (royal) dignity [and] status. 1. When you see the ever changing seasons (?), rains [and] heat (?)
b5 ... the ... which cause longing, (when you) ... in the rivulets of water dug by nature
b6 ... you will ... like being between ... certainly delight [in]. 2. (The screeching (?)) of the flamingos, peacocks, koels (?) ...</item>
